roundDescription: (16 points) I'll give you a list of four things in a specified group. Only two of those things fit the category. Give me both answers for a point apiece.

questions.questionText: Animals that lay eggs: Echidnas, Okapis, Pangolins, Wasps.
Animated shows streaming on Netflix: Arcane, Castlevania, The Legend of Vox Machina, X-Men '97.
First season SNL cast members: Dan Aykroyd, Eddie Murphy, Bill Murray, Laraine Newman.
Died during the Titanic sinking: Captain Edward Smith, director J. Bruce Ismay, socialite Margaret Brown, tycoon John Jacob Astor IV.
questions.answerText: Captain Edward Smith|John Jacob Astor IV

questions.questionText: Members of the EU: Georgia, Greece, Portugal, Switzerland.
NFL teams that have fired their head coaches this year: Bengals, Jets, Saints, Vikings.
Cities that are home to one of these mind-bending Meow Wolf art installations: Denver, Las Vegas, Phoenix, Portland.
Elements named after places: Fermium, Gallium, Holmium, Seaborgium.
Bonus: Including some nice shots of the Legacy Ottoman Hotel, "Taken 2" is mostly set in what city that's about 65% European?
